                                                                            <comments>
                            <comment id="210309" author="mdiep" created="Wed, 4 Oct 2017 16:36:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;files have been uploaded as requested&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="210255" author="brian" created="Tue, 3 Oct 2017 20:27:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;While we are here, shouldn&apos;t&#160;&lt;a href=&quot;https://build.whamcloud.com/jobs-pub/lustre-b2_10/configurations/axis-arch/x86_64/axis-build_type/server/axis-distro/el7/axis-ib_stack/inkernel/builds/30/archive/artifacts/RPMS/x86_64/spl-dkms-0.7.1-1.el7.noarch.rpm&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;spl-dkms-0.7.1-1.el7.noarch.rpm&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&quot;https://build.whamcloud.com/jobs-pub/lustre-b2_10/configurations/axis-arch/x86_64/axis-build_type/server/axis-distro/el7/axis-ib_stack/inkernel/builds/30/archive/artifacts/RPMS/x86_64/zfs-dkms-0.7.1-1.el7.noarch.rpm&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;zfs-dkms-0.7.1-1.el7.noarch.rpm&lt;/a&gt; also, uncontroversially, be in the download repo since they are by definition source code only?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="210251" author="pjones" created="Tue, 3 Oct 2017 20:19:02 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Then I think that should be fine&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="210248" author="brian" created="Tue, 3 Oct 2017 20:13:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;To be clear, what we would like to see added to the &lt;a href=&quot;https://downloads.hpdd.intel.com/public/lustre/lustre-2.10.1/el7/server/RPMS/x86_64/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;download repo&lt;/a&gt; are the &lt;a href=&quot;https://build.whamcloud.com/jobs-pub/lustre-b2_10/configurations/axis-arch/x86_64/axis-build_type/server/axis-distro/el7/axis-ib_stack/inkernel/builds/30/archive/artifacts/RPMS/x86_64/zfs-0.7.1-1.el7.x86_64.rpm&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;zfs-0.7.1-1.el7.x86_64.rpm&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&quot;https://build.whamcloud.com/jobs-pub/lustre-b2_10/configurations/axis-arch/x86_64/axis-build_type/server/axis-distro/el7/axis-ib_stack/inkernel/builds/30/archive/artifacts/RPMS/x86_64/spl-0.7.1-1.el7.x86_64.rpm&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;spl-0.7.1-1.el7.x86_64.rpm&lt;/a&gt; RPMs that are currently available in the &lt;a href=&quot;https://build.whamcloud.com/jobs-pub/lustre-b2_10/configurations/axis-arch/x86_64/axis-build_type/server/axis-distro/el7/axis-ib_stack/inkernel/builds/30/archive/artifacts/RPMS/x86_64/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;2.10.1&lt;/a&gt; Jenkins build, openly downloadable without authentication. These would be the parallel RPMs that we got permission to distribute with IML 3.x because they are the userspace RPMs only.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This would imply inclusion of the dependent userspace libs:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;libuutil1-0.7.1-1.el7.x86_64.rpm
libzfs2-0.7.1-1.el7.x86_64.rpm
libzfs2-devel-0.7.1-1.el7.x86_64.rpm
libzpool2-0.7.1-1.el7.x86_64.rpm&#160;

&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="210244" author="utopiabound" created="Tue, 3 Oct 2017 19:46:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Oh I understand.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The following lack the same ZFS rpms that build.hpdd.intel.com has available:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://downloads.hpdd.intel.com/public/lustre/lustre-2.10.0/el7/server/RPMS/x86_64/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://downloads.hpdd.intel.com/public/lustre/lustre-2.10.0/el7/server/RPMS/x86_64/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://downloads.hpdd.intel.com/public/lustre/lustre-2.10.1/el7/server/RPMS/x86_64/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://downloads.hpdd.intel.com/public/lustre/lustre-2.10.1/el7/server/RPMS/x86_64/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
